    <name>Evidence-Based Instructional Design Principles</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NRC Design Principles&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;"&gt;The National Research Council (NRS) report identified evidence-based principles for related to motivation, engagement, and learning. Among these design principles are...&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Build learners’ self-efficacy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Help learners to set appropriate and realistic goals&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Offer accurate and timely feedback in ways that motivate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Use assessments appropriately&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Provide choice and autonomy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Offer learners meaningful choices&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Use and inspire learners’ interests&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;span size="3"&gt;Encourage collaboration and cooperation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3" face="Calibri"&gt;Help learners overcome barriers to persistence&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3" face="Calibri"&gt;Select &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;one&lt;/span&gt; of the design principles listed above, in the discussion forum explain why this principle has meaning for you, and suggest concrete strategies for incorporating that principle into your instructional design. For example, if you select &lt;i&gt;Help learners to set appropriate and realistic goals&lt;/i&gt;, list specific actions of the teacher to incorporate this design principle into instruction. Read postings that your fellow course participants make to the other design principles and add comments, sharing your experiences and thoughts, as appropriate.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: verdana, arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small;" size="3" face="Calibri"&gt;Click below on "Add a new discussion topic" to share your response.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
